# Validation Phase

When validating an implementation:

## Systematic Validation

For each plan phase:
1. Verify checkmarks match actual completion
2. Run all automated verification commands
3. List manual testing steps for the user
4. Consider edge cases and regressions

## Validation Report Structure

- Implementation status per phase
- Automated verification results (pass/fail)
- Code review: matches plan, deviations, potential issues
- Manual testing required
- Recommendations

## Checklist

- [ ] All phases marked complete are actually done
- [ ] Automated tests pass
- [ ] Code follows existing patterns
- [ ] No regressions introduced
- [ ] Error handling is robust

## Recommended Order

1. Implement → 2. Commit → 3. Validate → 4. PR description
